- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses closure properties of jumping finite automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with formal models of computation. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of jumping finite automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) may also be relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of jumping finite automata and their relation to other models studied in the literature.
